Filmed in Olivebridge, New York, September 2019
Studio Photography May 2014: IJ.Biermann
ECM50 | 1969-2019 is a series of 50+1 documentary short films by IJB

On the occasion of Gary Peacock's 80th birthday, ECM released "Now This", the first album of his trio with Marc Copland on piano and Joey Baron on drums.

Gary Peacock – bass
Marc Copland – piano
Joey Baron – drums
Recorded July 2014, Rainbow Studio, Oslo
Engineer: Jan Erik Kongshaug
Cover Photo: Eliott Peacock
Design: Sascha Kleis
Produced by Manfred Eicher
Released on ECM Records, May 2015
℗ © 2015 ECM Records GmbH München

In the realm of the piano trio the bar is set high, and creative bassist Gary Peacock has helped raise it in the groups of Bill Evans, Paul Bley and Keith Jarrett. Now This is an album with the bassist’s current trio, recorded last summer in Oslo. Powerful new versions of some Peacock classics – such as “Moor”, “Vignette”, “Requiem” and “Gaya” – are interspersed with recent compositions. Marc Copland and Joey Baron each contribute tunes, and the group also tackles Scott La Faro’s “Gloria’s Step”. In this band, roles are very evenly shared, and this is an optimum context in which to appreciate the melodic invention of Peacock’s bass playing. Marc Copland always honours the needs of the compositions and Joey Baron supplies both drive and sensitive detail. ecmrecords.com/shop/143038752066/now-this-gary-peacock-trio
title: ECM50 | 2015 Gary Peacock & Marc Copland
